{"version":"https://jsonfeed.org/version/1","title":"python ✧ errbufferoverfl","description":"Recent content in python on errbufferoverfl","home_page_url":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/","feed_url":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/tags/python/index.json","items":[{"title":"Bookmarks","date_published":"2023-07-14T11:55:04+10:00","date_modified":"2023-07-14T11:59:06+10:00","id":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/notes/bookmarks/","url":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/notes/bookmarks/","content_html":"\u003ch2 id=\"python\"\u003ePython\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://sagarkaurav.hashnode.dev/tracking-database-changes-in-flask-sqlalchemy-for-audit-logs\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eTracking database changes in Flask Sqlalchemy for audit logs\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"oauth\"\u003eOAuth\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/rfc7591/\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eOAuth 2.0 Dynamic Client Registration Protocol\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n"},{"title":"Using Pytest with Flask","date_published":"2023-07-14T11:44:22+10:00","date_modified":"2023-07-15T13:08:30+10:00","id":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/notes/using-pytest-with-flask/","url":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/notes/using-pytest-with-flask/","content_html":"\u003ch2 id=\"what-to-test\"\u003eWhat to test?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnit tests should focus on testing a small unit of code in isolation:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDatabase models\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUtility functions\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFunctional tests should focus on how the view functions operate:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNominal conditions (GET, POST, etc.) for a view function\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInvalid HTTP methods are handled properly for a view function\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInvalid data is passed to a view function\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"documenting-tests\"\u003eDocumenting Tests\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMartin Fowler provides a really idiomatic way of describing tests in his blog post on \n\u003ca href=\"https://martinfowler.com/bliki/GivenWhenThen.html\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eGivenWhenThen\u003c/a\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"chroma\"\u003e\n\u003ctable class=\"lntable\"\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e1\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e2\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e3\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e4\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e5\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-python\" data-lang=\"python\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003eGIVEN a User model\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003eWHEN a new User is created\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003eTHEN check the email, hashed_password, and role fields are defined correctly\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGIVEN - what are the initial conditions for the test?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWHEN - what is occurring that needs to be tested?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTHEN - what is the expected response?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"testing-for-exceptions\"\u003eTesting for Exceptions\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAsserting an exception \u003cstrong\u003eis\u003c/strong\u003e raised:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"chroma\"\u003e\n\u003ctable class=\"lntable\"\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e1\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e2\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e3\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e4\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e5\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-python\" data-lang=\"python\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"kn\"\u003eimport\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nn\"\u003epytest\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003edef\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nf\"\u003etest_raises_exception\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e():\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003ewith\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003epytest\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eraises\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"ne\"\u003eZeroDivisionError\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e):\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e        \u003cspan class=\"mi\"\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e/\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"mi\"\u003e0\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eAsserting an exception \u003cstrong\u003eis not\u003c/strong\u003e raised:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"chroma\"\u003e\n\u003ctable class=\"lntable\"\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e 1\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e 2\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e 3\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e 4\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e 5\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e 6\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e 7\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e 8\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e 9\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e10\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e11\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-python\" data-lang=\"python\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003edef\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nf\"\u003emy_division_function\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003ea\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e,\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eb\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e):\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003ereturn\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003ea\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e/\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eb\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003edef\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nf\"\u003etest_code_raises_no_exception\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e():\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e    Assert your python code raises no exception.    \n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e    \u0026#34;\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003etry\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e:\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e        \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003emy_division_function\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"mi\"\u003e10\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e,\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"mi\"\u003e5\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eexcept\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"ne\"\u003eZeroDivisionError\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eas\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eexc\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e:\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e        \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eassert\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"kc\"\u003eFalse\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e,\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"sa\"\u003ef\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e\u0026#34;\u0026#39;10 / 5\u0026#39; raised an exception \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"si\"\u003e{\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eexc\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"si\"\u003e}\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e\u0026#34;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"pytest-fixtures\"\u003ePytest Fixtures\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFixtures initialise tests to a known state to run tests in a predictable and repeatable manner, these should be created in your \u003ccode\u003econftest.py\u003c/code\u003e file.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn Pytest, fixtures can be run with different scopes:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003efunction\u003c/code\u003e - run once per test function (default scope)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eclass\u003c/code\u003e - run once per test class\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003emodule\u003c/code\u003e - run once per module (e.g., a test file)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003esession\u003c/code\u003e - run once per session\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor example, to create a User as a fixture:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"chroma\"\u003e\n\u003ctable class=\"lntable\"\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e1\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e2\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e3\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e4\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e5\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e6\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-python\" data-lang=\"python\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"kn\"\u003efrom\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nn\"\u003eproject.models\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"kn\"\u003eimport\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eUser\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"nd\"\u003e@pytest\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003efixture\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003escope\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e=\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u0026#39;module\u0026#39;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003edef\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nf\"\u003enew_user\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e():\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003euser\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e=\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eUser\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u0026#39;username@example.com\u0026#39;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e,\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u0026#39;Password1!\u0026#39;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003ereturn\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003euser\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e@pytest.fixture(scope='module')\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis decorator specifies that a function is a fixture with a module-level scope. So this fixture will be called once per test module.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003edef new_user()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs the function that creates an instance of a User using valid arguments.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo use this fixture, in other tests you pass it in as the first argument to a subsequent test, e.g.,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"chroma\"\u003e\n\u003ctable class=\"lntable\"\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e1\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e2\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e3\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e4\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e5\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e6\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e7\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e8\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"lnt\"\u003e9\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd class=\"lntd\"\u003e\n\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" class=\"chroma\"\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-python\" data-lang=\"python\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003edef\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"nf\"\u003etest_new_user_with_fixture\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003enew_user\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"p\"\u003e):\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e    GIVEN a User model\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e    WHEN a new User is created\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e    THEN check the email, hashed_password, and role fields are defined correctly\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"s2\"\u003e    \u0026#34;\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eassert\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003enew_user\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003eemail\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e==\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u0026#39;username@example.com\u0026#39;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eassert\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003enew_user\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003ehashed_password\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e!=\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u0026#39;Password1!\u0026#39;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"line\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"cl\"\u003e    \u003cspan class=\"k\"\u003eassert\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003enew_user\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"n\"\u003erole\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"o\"\u003e==\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"s1\"\u003e\u0026#39;user\u0026#39;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e"},{"title":"Interesting Tech Tools","date_published":"2023-06-28T21:08:38+10:00","date_modified":"2023-07-09T12:35:50+10:00","id":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/notes/interesting-tech-tools/","url":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/notes/interesting-tech-tools/","content_html":"\u003ch2 id=\"distributed-computing\"\u003eDistributed Computing\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"distributed-press\"\u003eDistributed Press\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://distributed.press/\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eWebsite\u003c/a\u003e  ·  \n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/hyphacoop/api.distributed.press\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eGithub Repo\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ean open source publishing tool for the World Wide Web and [[Distributed Web]]. It automates publishing to the world wide web, and seeds to \n\n\n\n\n\n\u003ca\n  href=\"/notes/IPFS/\"\n  rel=\"noopener\" class=\"internal-link\"\n  data-src=\"/notes/IPFS/\"\u003eIPFS\u003c/a\u003e and \n\n\n\n\n\n\u003ca\n  href=\"/notes/Holepunch/\"\n  rel=\"noopener\" class=\"internal-link\"\n  data-src=\"/notes/Holepunch/\"\u003eHolepunch\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAdditional Notes\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003ca\n  href=\"/posts/setting-up-distributed-press-on-digital-ocean/\"\n  rel=\"noopener\" class=\"internal-link\"\n  data-src=\"/posts/setting-up-distributed-press-on-digital-ocean/\"\u003eSetting Up Distributed Press on Digital Ocean\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"microservices\"\u003eMicroservices\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"temporal\"\u003eTemporal\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://temporal.io/\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eWebsite\u003c/a\u003e · \n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/temporalio/temporal\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eGithub Repo\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAn open source programming model that can be used to provide in depth tracing using the concept of \u0026ldquo;business logic as code\u0026rdquo;.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"color--design\"\u003eColor \u0026amp; Design\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"dopely\"\u003eDopely\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA bunch of helpful colour tools like pallet, tone, tint and shade generators. Also has digital colour tools for checking contrast and colour blindcheckers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://colors.dopely.top/\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eDopely\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"software-development\"\u003eSoftware Development\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"refactoring-guru\"\u003eRefactoring Guru\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eProvides high-level and implementation guides for common design patterns and refactoring.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://refactoring.guru/\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eRefactoring Guru\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"python-patterns\"\u003ePython Patterns\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBrandon Rhodes, evolving guide to design patterns in the Python programming language. The site allows him to collect his ideas about Python and Design Patterns all in one place.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://python-patterns.guide/\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003ePython Patterns\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"flask-documentation\"\u003eFlask Documentation\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eComprehensive guide to Flask, that includes common patterns, how Flask works, and how to get started with common components, like SQL Lite.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/2.3.x/\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eFlask Documentation\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"graphs\"\u003eGraphs\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"cytoscapejs\"\u003eCytoscape.js\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGraph theory (network) library for visualisation and analysis.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://js.cytoscape.org/\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eCytoscape.js Official Website\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"title":"Snake Charming for Beginners","date_published":"2019-10-25T00:00:00+11:00","date_modified":"2023-05-28T00:00:00+10:00","id":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/soapbox/Snake-Charming-for-Beginners/","url":"https://garden.errbufferoverfl.me/soapbox/Snake-Charming-for-Beginners/","content_html":"\u003cp\u003eSnake-charming is an age-old practice of hypnotizing snakes by playing and waving a murli - in the modern day this practice looks much different, equipped with an Integrated Development Environment (IDE), a clackity keyboard and a trusty guide we\u0026rsquo;ll be taking you through how you can effectively charm Python 3.6.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOn the first day of our trek through the dense jungles of Pythonia we will be looking at how to build a simple sub-domain enumeration tool and how to get started building simple exploits - for those who have trekked these paths before - extra challenges will await you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDay two we will move further into the dark jungles of Pythonia delving into forbidden user-land territory and how you can use Python to gather useful system-level information, and contact the UNIX daemons of old.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhile writing this training description, errbufferoverfl wrote two Python fan fictions, the next cyber-themed Hollywood blockbuster and a Shakespearian play about the training.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://errbufferoverfl.github.io/snake-charming/\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eGitHub\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n"}]}